The paper focuses on multi-arm manipulation tasks in warehouse and manufacturing environments, which involves motion planning and coordination of multiple robots. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper leverages recent advances in multi-robot motion planning for high DoF systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with optimization and computational challenges, which suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel multi-modal extension of the dRRT* algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the approach and compares it to alternatives, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
